alecoyneracing.com/2020/01/23/ferrucci-to-drive-no-18-sealmaster-dale-coyne-racing-with-vasser-sullivan-entry-for-2020-ntt-indycar-season/|title=Ferrucci to Drive No. 18 SealMaster Dale Coyne Racing with Vasser-Sullivan Entry for 2020 NTT IndyCar Season|date=January 23, 2020|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n|All\n|-\n| [[DragonSpeed]]<ref name=\"DragonSpeed 6\">{{Cite news|url=https://racer.com/2019/12/24/dragonspeed-to-run-six-race-indycar-program-in-2020/|title=DragonSpeed to run six-race IndyCar program in 2020|last=Pruett|first=Marshall|date=December 24, 2019|work=Racer.com}}</ref>\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| 81\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of None.svg}} TBA{{refn|group=N|[[Ben Hanley]] was entered in the No. 81 at the March 15 St. Petersburg race, but the race was cancelled before Hanley could compete.}}\n|1, 8\u20139, 12\u201313, 15\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Dreyer & Reinbold Racing]]<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://racer.com/2020/01/07/dreyer-reinbold-expands-indycar-program-for-2020/|title=Dreyer & Reinbold expands IndyCar program for 2020|date=January 7, 2020|website=RACER|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Citrone-Buhl\">{{Cite web|url=https://racer.com/2020/02/21/citrone-buhl-autosport-plan-indycar-return/|title=UPDATED: Citrone/Buhl Autosport plan IndyCar return|last=Pruett|first=Marshall|date=February 21, 2020|website=[[Racer (magazine)|RACER]]|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Chevrolet]] \n|24\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Sage Karam]]<ref name=\"DRR increase\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/motor/2020/01/09/dreyer-and-reinbold-racing-bumping-up-indycar-program-three-races/4420977002/|title=Dreyer and Reinbold Racing increasing IndyCar race count: 'We've got a lot to learn'|last=Brown|first=Nathan|date=January 10, 2020|website=[[The Indianapolis Star|IndyStar]]|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n|4\u20135, 9, 15\n|-\n|TBA{{refn|group=N|Dreyer and Reinbold have previously used the No. 48, but that number was bought by [[Arrow McLaren SP]] on March 5, 2020.}}\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of None.svg}} TBA\n|9\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Ed Carpenter Racing]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Chevrolet]] \n|rowspan=\"2\"|20\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Conor Daly]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://racer.com/2019/12/09/daly-lands-ecr-road-course-seat/|title=Daly lands ECR road course seat|date=December 9, 2019|website=RACER|language=en|access-date=2019-12-09}}</ref>\n|2, 4\u20135, 8, 11\u201315\n|-\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Ed Carpenter (racing driver)|Ed Carpenter]]\n|1, 3, 6\u20137, 9\u201310\n|-\n|21\n|{{flagicon|NLD}} [[Rinus VeeKay]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nl.motorsport.com/indycar/news/rinus-van-kalmthout-debuut-indycar-series-2020-carpenter-racing/4596699/|title=Officieel: Van Kalmthout debuteert volgend jaar in IndyCar|last=Vording|first=Ronald|work=Motorsport.com|date=November 20, 2019|accessdate=November 20, 2019}}</ref> {{Color box|orange|R|border=darkgray}}\n|All\n|-\n|TBA\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Conor Daly]]<ref name=\":1\"/>\n|9\n|-\n|[[Michael Shank|Meyer Shank Racing]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/indycar/news/meyer-shank-full-time-andretti/4594508/|title=Meyer Shank goes full-time for 2020 with Andretti alliance|last=Malsher|first=David|work=Motorsport.com|date=November 9, 2019|accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref> \n|[[Honda Performance Development|Honda]]\n|60\n|{{flagicon|UK}} [[Jack Harvey (racing driver)|Jack Harvey]]\n|All\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rahal Letterman Lanigan Racing]]<ref>{{cite web|title=RLL closing in on third car|url=https://racer.com/2019/08/07/rll-closing-in-on-third-car/|last=Pruett|first=Marshall|work=Racer.com|publisher=Racer.com|date=August 7, 2019|accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Honda Performance Development|Honda]]\n|15\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Graham Rahal]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us.motorsport.com/indycar/news/rahal-extends-contract-with-rllr-in-five-year-deal-1045162/3118567/|title=Rahal extends contract with RLLR in five-year deal|work=[[Motorspo